<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-07-07T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-07-07T02:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 M 221/143: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-07-07T15:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">July 7,
                                        1925—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 7—8:37
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>266. From MacMurray: Arrived today. Mayer will remain in charge pending
                            consultations with colleagues as to proposed presentation of letters of
                            credence to Tuan as Provisional Chief Executive.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>